title: ShowingAlertDialog: Changed visibility of ShowingAlertDialog.alertDialog from…
message:
ShowingAlertDialog: Changed visibility of ShowingAlertDialog.alertDialog from package back to private.  Two commits ago I changed it so that ExcludeCellsAlertDialog could see it.  In this revision I change ExcludeCellsAlertDialog's superclass from ShowingAlertDialog to ActivityAlertDialog and give ExcludeCellsAlertDialog its own alertDialog field so ExcludeCellsAlertDialog no longer needs to (nor can it) see alertDialog.

title: InternalItemsAlertDialog, TemplateOptionsAlertDialog, ExcludeAlertDialog:…
message:
InternalItemsAlertDialog, TemplateOptionsAlertDialog, ExcludeAlertDialog: InternalItemsAlertDialog has two subclasses: TemplateOptionsAlertDialog and ExcludeAlertDialog.  Before, both had to be configured only once before the first show().  Now, ExcludeAlertDialog is changed so that it has to be configured not just once before the first show() but also before every show().  I could have just created ExcludeAlertDialog.show(templateModel) and left InternalItemsAlertDialog and TemplateOptionsAlertDialog alone but that would mean a third, new subclass of InternalItemsAlertDialog that should be configured before every show() may be flawed.  How?  If show() is not overridden or replaced the inherited show() might be used as is and this (old) inherited show() only configures once before the first show().  The new show() ensures configured == true.
ShowingAlertDialog, ExcludeCellsAlertDialog: Changed visibility of ShowingAlertDialog.alertDialog from private to package so that ExcludeCellsAlertDialog can prevent it from dismissing when the positive button is clicked if amount is < 1.
ExcludeAlertDialog, TemplateCreator: Increased encapsulation by getting the excluded rows, cols, and cells instead of making customer (TemplateCreator) do it.

message: Main: Improved insertGrid() by passing it a PartialTemplateModel instead of just a templateId. Also, a "global" reference to this.templateModel in order to call getFirstOptionalFieldValue() is avoiding, reducing coupling.

title: TemplatesTable: Replaced getByType() with exists().  Although both methods have…

TemplatesTable: Replaced getByType() with exists().  Although both methods have the same input and the same output they differ in that exists() does not have the side effect getByType() has: it doesn't copy() cursor to the instance's fields.
